 with the collaboration of Phyllis Kaberry and E. M. Chilver soon after the Second World War and continues to this day. The idea for this book arose from a concern to recognize the continuing influence of E. M. Chilver on a wide variety of social, historical, political and economic studies. The result is a volume with a broad historical scope yet one that also focuses on major contemporary theoretical issues such as the meaning and construction of ethnic identities and the anthropological study of historical processes. For more information on this title and related publications, go to http://lucy.ukc.ac.uk/Chilver/index.html  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aEthnologyzCameroon. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aArdener, Shirley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAusten, Ralph A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurnham, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChem-Langhêê, Bongfen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFanso, Verkijika G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFardon, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFowler, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFowler, Ian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGeary, Christraud M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLukong Banadzem, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Neil, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTardits, Claude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWarnier, Jean-Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocab